{"info": {"author": "Dimitri Merejkowsky", "author_email": "d.merej@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "description": "# kak-spell\n\nPyEnchant wrapper for Kakoune.\n\n## Installation\n\n\n1. Install the Enchant library, and the required dictionaries. See [PyEnchant documentation](https://pyenchant.github.io/pyenchant/install.html) for details.\n\n2. Install the `kak-spell` script, for instance with [pipx](https://pipxproject.github.io/pipx/):\n\n```\npipx install kak-spell\n```\n\n3. Install [plug.kak](https://github.com/andreyorst/plug.kak) and add the following lines in your `kakrc`:\n\n```kak\nplug \"dmerejkowsky/kak-spell\"\n\ndefine-command lint-on-save \"hook buffer BufWritePre .* lint\"```\n```\n\n\n4. (optional): declare a user mode and some mappings:\n\n```kak\ndeclare-user-mode kak-spell\nmap global user s ': enter-user-mode kak-spell<ret>' -docstring 'enter spell user mode'\nmap global kak-spell e ': kak-spell %opt{spell_lang}<ret>' -docstring \"enable spell checking\"\nmap global kak-spell c ': kak-spell-clear<ret>' -docstring 'clear spelling highlighters'\nmap global kak-spell n ': kak-spell-next<ret>' -docstring 'go to next spell error'\nmap global kak-spell r ': kak-spell-replace<ret>' -docstring 'suggest a list of replacements'\nmap global kak-spell a ': kak-spell-add<ret>' -docstring 'add the selection to the user dict'\nmap global kak-spell x ': kak-spell-remove<ret>' -docstring 'remove the selection from the user dict'\n```\n\n\n\n## Discuss\n\nYou can discuss features of this plugin on [discuss.kakoune.com](https://discuss.kakoune.com/t/alternate-implementation-for-spell-checker/781).\n\nI'd like to thank all the people who contributed code and ideas to make usage of this plugin easier.\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/dmerejkowsky/kak-spell", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "kak-spell", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/kak-spell/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/kak-spell/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/dmerejkowsky/kak-spell"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/kak-spell/0.2.1/", "requires_dist": ["attrs (>=19.3.0,<20.0.0)", "path (>=13.1.0,<14.0.0)", "pyxdg (>=0.26,<0.27)", "pyenchant (==3.0.1)"], "requires_python": ">=3.6,<4.0", "summary": "PyEnchant wrapper for Kakoune", "version": "0.2.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>kak-spell</h1>\n<p>PyEnchant wrapper for Kakoune.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Install the Enchant library, and the required dictionaries. See <a href=\"https://pyenchant.github.io/pyenchant/install.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">PyEnchant documentation</a> for details.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Install the <code>kak-spell</code> script, for instance with <a href=\"https://pipxproject.github.io/pipx/\" rel=\"nofollow\">pipx</a>:</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<pre><code>pipx install kak-spell\n</code></pre>\n<ol>\n<li>Install <a href=\"https://github.com/andreyorst/plug.kak\" rel=\"nofollow\">plug.kak</a> and add the following lines in your <code>kakrc</code>:</li>\n</ol>\n<pre>plug \"dmerejkowsky/kak-spell\"\n\ndefine-command lint-on-save \"hook buffer BufWritePre .* lint\"```\n</pre>\n<ol>\n<li>(optional): declare a user mode and some mappings:</li>\n</ol>\n<pre>declare-user-mode kak-spell\nmap global user s ': enter-user-mode kak-spell&lt;ret&gt;' -docstring 'enter spell user mode'\nmap global kak-spell e ': kak-spell %opt{spell_lang}&lt;ret&gt;' -docstring \"enable spell checking\"\nmap global kak-spell c ': kak-spell-clear&lt;ret&gt;' -docstring 'clear spelling highlighters'\nmap global kak-spell n ': kak-spell-next&lt;ret&gt;' -docstring 'go to next spell error'\nmap global kak-spell r ': kak-spell-replace&lt;ret&gt;' -docstring 'suggest a list of replacements'\nmap global kak-spell a ': kak-spell-add&lt;ret&gt;' -docstring 'add the selection to the user dict'\nmap global kak-spell x ': kak-spell-remove&lt;ret&gt;' -docstring 'remove the selection from the user dict'\n</pre>\n<h2>Discuss</h2>\n<p>You can discuss features of this plugin on <a href=\"https://discuss.kakoune.com/t/alternate-implementation-for-spell-checker/781\" rel=\"nofollow\">discuss.kakoune.com</a>.</p>\n<p>I'd like to thank all the people who contributed code and ideas to make usage of this plugin easier.</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7009358, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "4d3c9de2876d77676d8cc8e16c3ee566", "sha256": "c8e2935cd46f83bbff476e83d22927d8b3582fc0ffe4b0816e4db599cae95a8a"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "kak_spell-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "4d3c9de2876d77676d8cc8e16c3ee566", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.7,<4.0", "size": 4477, "upload_time": "2020-02-28T10:19:32", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-28T10:19:32.692871Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/e5/a6/7dc2a15ca33302cd9849567e7e68929d7132191d221f2d602d0d3846a9b4/kak_spell-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "abf410569b61d688cfaff4c341acecfa", "sha256": "e724813a9c1fe56d4e8cc941463848a0ce3451abd0a587522d28b486be2e6a0a"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "kak-spell-0.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "abf410569b61d688cfaff4c341acecfa", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.7,<4.0", "size": 4110, "upload_time": "2020-02-28T10:19:30", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-28T10:19:30.082780Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/0b/85/9790ae5a8befef060c3f9c85fb9558abcd486672043d9755bee7b7bebc5e